The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, April 22, 2004 				 Is there a need for global culture?
																								As part of a series of conferences on Notions of Progress in Different Cultures, Max Mueller Bhavan Calcutta and The German Agency for Technical Co-operation jointly host Does Culture Make a Difference?  a conference on progress and development in India. It focuses on issues related to the advancement of India, at the same time examining whether the Indian culture has an influence on the progress and development of its people. It raises pertinent questions regarding the progress of the human race and its relevance to, and direct dependence on, technology and science as we know it today. Discussions among eminent teachers and thinkers of our times will explain the relationship between culture and socio-economic development in India, particularly in the complex contexts of globalisation and trans-cultural and international interaction. The objective of all these discussions will be to seek an honest answer to the question as to whether a common world culture is most favourable for developing healthy international relations within the global community.																								Event: Conference on Progress and Development in India																								When: April 22 - 24; 9.30 am																								Where: Taj Bengal
